<item>
            <title>[FLINK-18074] Confirm checkpoint completed on task side would not fail the task if exception thrown out</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-18074</link>
                <project id="12315522" key="FLINK">Flink</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-17350&quot; title=&quot;StreamTask should always fail immediately on failures in synchronous part of a checkpoint&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;FLINK-17350&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;FLINK-17350&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; let the task fail immediately once sync phase of checkpoint failed. However, the included commit &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/flink/pull/12101/commits/a2cd3daceca16ae841119d94a24328b4af37dcd8&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;&apos;Simplify checkpoint exception handling&apos;&lt;/a&gt; actually would not fail the task if the runnable of &lt;tt&gt;() -&amp;gt; notifyCheckpointComplete&lt;/tt&gt; throwing exception out.&lt;br/&gt;
In a nutshell, this actually changes previous checkpoint exception handling.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Moreover, that part of code also affect the implemented code of &lt;tt&gt;notifyCheckpointAbortAsync&lt;/tt&gt; when I introduce &lt;tt&gt;notifyCheckpointAborted&lt;/tt&gt; on task side. &lt;/p&gt;</description>
